{{short description|American energy efficiency program}}
'''Efficiency Vermont''' is a program that promotes and facilitates [[Efficient energy use|energy efficiency]] across the state of Vermont. Created in 2000 at the behest of the [[Vermont Public Service Board]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://psb.vermont.gov/utilityindustries/eeu/generalinfo/creationandstructure |title=Energy Efficiency Utility Creation and Structure &#124; Vermont Public Service Board |publisher=Psb.vermont.gov |date= |accessdate=2013-09-08}}</ref> it has substantially reduced electrical demand and more than balanced load growth in recent years.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://psb.vermont.gov/utilityindustries/eeu/generalinfo/evtaccomplishments |title=Efficiency Vermont's Accomplishments &#124; Vermont Public Service Board |publisher=Psb.vermont.gov |date= |accessdate=2013-09-08}}</ref> It is sometimes referred to as an energy efficiency utility.<ref>{{cite web|last=Arterian |first=Susan |url=http://spectrum.ieee.org/green-tech/conservation/the-rise-of-the-energy-efficiency-utility |title=The Rise of the Energy Efficiency Utility - IEEE Spectrum |publisher=Spectrum.ieee.org |date=2008-05-01 |accessdate=2013-09-08}}</ref> It is operated by the nonprofit [[Vermont Energy Investment Corporation]].

